 BARBERTON – A tourist from New Caledonia in Australia, who went missing for a day while on holiday in the area, has been found alive and unharmed According to Lionel Meyer, a co-owner of Bubez Guesthouse, Joanna Maria Legras was reportedly missing on Sunday afternoon. He said Legras has a health condition that may have contributed to her disappearance, according to his husband. “Her missing was reported to the Barberton SAPS and Hi-Tec Security. A search was established. She was found the next day at Phoenix Hotel unharmed. Some tourists from Botswana had offered her a shelter there at Phoenix,” said Meyer. Read More: Woman who went missing found safe and unharmed 